features: 【Ergonomic Lumbar Support】The ergonomically designed backrest of our ergonomic office chair has prominent lumbar support to fit the natural curvature of the spine. The Computer Desk Chair with mid-back brings quality and comfort to any office.

【Comfortable Seat】Ergonomic features an all-elastic premium mesh back and a high-density sponge seat making the mesh office chair a good choice for all-day comfortable office seating. The unique mesh design is skin-friendly and breathable, which keeps you cool all day.

【Space-saving】Flip-up armrests are available and won't be in your way when not in use. The Armrests of the computer chair provide comfortable support for your arms and can be flipped up to save space effectively while not in use. It is perfect for the office, bedroom, study room, living room, or gaming room.

【Adjustable Headrest】The Unique Headrest easily adjusts to your requirements. More support for the head and neck can be provided by adjusting the height and angle of the headrest, which can make you feel comfortable and help you avoid soreness from your neck and back!

【Multifunctional Mechanism】The seat height of this 360° Rotating chair could be easily adjusted by the pneumatic adjustment lever, and the adjustment range is 18.5-22.2 inches. Besides, the rocking mode from 107° to 144° helps you to relax from hard work.

【Smooth Movement & Stability】Our comfy office desk chair comes with smooth and multi-direction casters, which allow you to move the chair around effortlessly. They can run smoothly on tile, wooden floors, carpets, and other floorings. The large 5-star base increases stability even at the full height range. The maximum weight capacity is 250 lbs.

【Easy Assembly】The home office chair comes with installation instructions and all necessary hardware& tools. We also offer a video to help you, allowing the office chair installation to be completed within 10-15 minutes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good value office chair
reviews.reviewText: I ordered this to replace my previous office chair. I purchased one on sale at Fry's a few years ago, and it didn't even last a year. I have to keep it backed against a wall because the seat back won't support *any* weight anymore. Nuts to that!This chair arrived efficiently packed in a compact box, which was nice. The directions were clear, and it was pretty easy to assemble. I had it together in maybe ten minutes.Visually, the chair is aesthetically pleasing. It's a good looking chair. Functionally, it doesn't have many frills, but it's very comfortable. I can sit in it for several hours at a time without discomfort. It adjusts up and down in a good range, you can swing the arms out of the way, and there is a pocket on the back. I'm not sure if it's for additional cushioning or storage, but I keep the installation instructions back there just in case. That's it for frills, and for the price, that's just fine. I don't regret this chair, and it's already outlasted my previous one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to put together and sturdy
reviews.reviewText: I put this Office Chair, Desk Chair, Ergonomic Home Office Desk Chairs, Computer Chair with Flip up Armrests, Mesh Desk Chairs with Wheels, Office Desk Chair, Mid-Back Task Chair with Ergonomic Lumbar Support together in about half an hour. It was easy enough. My son has been sitting in this chair daily for about 2 months now and it’s still in one piece. So, I’m happy seeing he’s not the most careful, meaning this chair must be pretty sturdy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Basic but comfortable.
reviews.reviewText: This chair is comfortable and well padded. Doesn’t offer a ton of support but it’s shaped to conform to your back. I think I prefer chairs with arms for balance but for the price this is a decent chair. No frills but does the job. It was easy to put together.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Lumbar Support, Very Comfortable
reviews.reviewText: This office chair comes disassembled, but it is fairly easy to assemble using the clear step-by-step instructions. It took me about 45 minutes, from the time I opened the box until I was sitting in the chair.The main parts of the chair have identifying marks on them, L - for left, R - for right, and Front for Front (of the chair). The chair is held together by bolts which require an "allen head" wrench, which is included with the assembly parts. No other tools are needed to assemble the chair.I really like the lumbar support that this chair gives. The chair was nearly perfect to sit in the first time I sat in it. I needed to adjust the height to make it perfect. I also like how the back support is fixed, it does not adjust forward or backwards (sliding forwards or backwards) like some chairs do. The tension for the for rocking setting is easy to adjust, but the tension was set perfectly for me right out of the box.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Smart packaging and very easy to assemble
reviews.reviewText: Working from home, shouldn’t be uncomfortable, and this office chair really helps to ensure that it’s not anymore. I put this together for my significant other in our upstairs home office. It took me about 10 to 15 minutes to assemble. She tells me that the chair is incredibly comfortable, I think that it’s lightweight in the right ways and very attractive. The chair legs are sturdy, but thinner than the usual office chairs, giving it a sleek and modern look without sacrificing Structural integrity. The wheels on the legs, because I frankly don’t know what else to call them, spin, super easy and rotate. Super easy.This is everything that you would expect an office chair to have. You can raise the seat or lower it. You can relax the lumbar support when you need to and lean back. It’s a great chair to have.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent budget office chair
reviews.reviewText: This came well packaged and nothing was damaged during shipping. Everything is wrapped in bubble wrap and nicely packed. The instructions are simple and to the point. All the parts are labeled correctly and it only took me about 10 minutes to assemble this office chair.The build construction is very well made and all of the plastic parts are smooth with no jagged and/or sharp edges. The plastic is good quality, but be mindful that the arm rest are plastic. This should not be an issue, but it's something to note.I'm right at 6ft tall and 210 pounds with a medium build and this chair is comfortable for me to sit in while drawing for extended periods.Overall, this is a great office chair. The price is very good and is far better quality than other office chairs I've owned within the same price range. It's very comfortable and well made.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Easy to assemble and nice looking
reviews.reviewText: Assembling the chair is easy. It came with good instructions and clearly labeled screws and tools. Extra screws were also provided. It took less than 15min to setup. The chair is adjustable for height and how much force is needed for the chair to recline. It can also block reclining. Although it can recline, the chair forces good posture. You can't really sit too far back into the chair so you have to sit straight up. I guess that's good for work and posture but it does take away from comfort.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality value chair. I would order it again!
reviews.reviewText: This chair is simple, but excellent. I was a bit concerned about what the quality would be like (considering the price), but I'm extremely happy with the sturdiness of the plastic and metal components, and I'm also happy with the the quality of the fabric. There are a limited number of "features" (such as the only arm movements are folding up or down), but you have the primary adjustments including height and back (lean and lock). Overall, it is very comfortable and is a nice chair. I'm very happy with this order and would have ordered it again. 5 stars!
